=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Overviews_Operators_ex45 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_dark noisy sound, with noise characteristics, featuring very_slow attack and percussive envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, energy distribution is late, filtered with steep_rolloff character, and spectrally simple.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: very_slow
  brightness: very_dark
  crest_factor_db: percussive
  envelope_flatness: very_dynamic
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: noisy
  spectral_complexity_mean: simple
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: late

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 0.0000
  harmonic_decay_rate: 0.0000
  harmonic_regularity: 0.0000
  pitch_clarity: 0.0000
  inharmonicity: 0.0000
  type: noise
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -2.4391
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Operators Example 45
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Overviews/Operators.html
// Tags: Operators, Overviews
// ---
// --- Example 45 ---
{ LFNoise0.ar(50, 0.5) thresh: 0.45 }.play // a low-rent gate
